14 WHEREAS, his thesis was "Neighborhood Revitalization: An Analysis of Neighborhood
15 Conditions in Atlanta's West End," and it helped to solidify the structure of the emerging
16 West End Neighborhood Development (WEND) organization; and
17 WHEREAS, over the years, he served in various leadership positions in WEND as well as
18 with the Beautification and Environmental Health Committee, the Piedmont Park
19 Conservancy, the Atlanta Urban Design, the Joel Chandler Harris Association (Wren's Nest),
20 the Atlanta Preservation Center, and the City of Atlanta Comprehensive Historic Resources
21 Survey Steering Committee; and
22 WHEREAS, for 34 years, Handy worked with the State of Georgia Department of Natural
23 Resources in the Division of Planning and Research undertaking statewide planning efforts
24 and developing numerous parks around the state; and
25 WHEREAS, Handy's significant organizational and leadership talents, remarkable patience
26 and diplomacy, keen sense of vision, and sensitivity to the needs of the citizens of this state
27 have earned him the respect and admiration of his community; and
28 WHEREAS, he is a person of magnanimous strengths with an unimpeachable reputation for
29 integrity, intelligence, fairness, and kindness; and
30 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
31 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
32 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
33 recognize and commend Handy Johnson, Jr., for his efficient, effective, unselfish, and
